This README file contains information on the contents of the meta-sip-custom layer.

Please see the corresponding sections below for details.

Dependencies
============

This layer depends on the following layers:

  - `meta`
  - `meta-python`

Ensure that these layers are included in your build environment before adding `meta-sip-custom`.

Patches
=======

Please submit any patches against the meta-sip-custom layer to the GitHub repository issues or pull requests.

Maintainer: Chetan Dandolu <chetan@novelmicrodevices.com>

Table of Contents
=================

  I. Adding the meta-sip-custom layer to your build
 II. SIP 6.8.6 recipe

I. Adding the meta-sip-custom layer to your build
=================================================

To include the meta-sip-custom layer in your build, add it to your `bblayers.conf` file:

```bash
bitbake-layers add-layer meta-sip-custom
```
II. SIP 6.8.6 recipe
====================

This layer currently includes the following recipe:

sip_6.8.6.bb: This recipe builds and installs SIP version 6.8.6, which is compatible with the ABI version of PyQt6.6.1. SIP is a tool for creating Python bindings for C and C++ libraries, and this version ensures compatibility with PyQt.